# Logistics Documentation Project

## Overview
This project explains how a basic logistics and transportation system works in real life.  
It is based on practical experience in airport transfer and transport services.

---

## 1. Booking Process
Customers make a booking through phone, app, or website.  
The system collects:
- Customer name  
- Pickup location  
- Destination  
- Time and date  

---

## 2. Dispatching
After receiving the booking, a dispatcher assigns a driver.  
The selection depends on:
- Driver availability  
- Location  
- Schedule

---

## 3. Driver Assignment
The driver receives the order details:
- Pickup point  
- Customer contact  
- Route information  

---

## 4. Pickup Process
Driver arrives at the location and picks up the customer.  
Communication is important to avoid delays.

---

## 5. Transportation
The trip starts from pickup location to destination.  
GPS tracking may be used to optimize the route.

---

## 6. Drop-off
Customer is safely dropped at the destination.  
The trip is completed in the system.

---

## 7. Common Issues in Logistics
- Delays due to traffic  
- Wrong location input  
- Communication problems  
- Vehicle availability issues  

---

## Conclusion
Logistics systems are based on coordination between customers, drivers, and dispatchers.  
Good communication and planning are key for success.
